<TITLE> Ex-CCF Gani jailed for 12 years for graft </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 5 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Thursday sentenced former Chief Conservator of Forests Osman Gani to 12 years in prison, Tk 10 lakh fine and another year's imprisonment for non-payment of the fines. Judge AKM Arifur Rahman of Special Judge's Court-10 set up in the Jatiya Sangsad Bhaban complex handed down the verdict. The court also sentenced Gani's wife Mahsin Ara Gani to three years in jail, Tk 1 lakh fine and another six months' imprisonment for failure to pay the fine for abetting her husband. The court at the same time ordered confiscation of the Gani couple's illegally amassed assets worth Tk 3.6 crore and 270 bharis of gold. Osman Gani is in jail but his wife is on the run. bdnews
